args.prompt:
You are given the opaque variable <query_llm_0/> which contains the output of a previous LLM call. It has a JSON array of task objects extracted from an email. Convert this JSON array into a sequence of tool calls that will perform these tasks using the functions available. For each task object, map it to one of these functions and provide the parameters exactly as the function expects. Produce valid JSON as the tool input for the multi_tool_use.parallel call. The structure should be:
{
  "tool_uses": [
    {"recipient_name": "functions.<function_name>", "parameters": { ... }},
    ...
  ]
}

Only include functions that match the action types: send_email -> functions.send_email, create_calendar_event -> functions.create_calendar_event, create_file -> functions.create_file, share_file -> functions.share_file, append_to_file -> functions.append_to_file. For any task with action "other_action", skip it (do not include it in tool_uses).

If a task parameter contains null values, include the keys with null values. If attachments contain filenames instead of file_ids, set attachments to null (we cannot attach files without file ids).

Do not include any comments or extra fields. Return only the JSON object for multi_tool_use.parallel. Use the values from <query_llm_0/> directly (they will be expanded).

